  <!-- ====== FAQ ====== -->
  <section class="lo-faq">
    <div class="lo-faq-inner">
      <div class="lo-faq-header">
        <span class="lo-sec-eyebrow">Questions</span>
        <h2 class="lo-sec-h2">Things parents <em>ask us</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="lo-faq-item">
        <div class="lo-faq-q">What exactly is a .com domain, and why does my child need one?</div>
        <p class="lo-faq-a">A .com domain is a unique address on the internet &mdash; like &ldquo;your-childs-name.com.&rdquo; Only one person can own each address. When you claim your child&rsquo;s name as a .com, nobody else in the world can ever use that exact address. As they grow up, it becomes their homepage, their portfolio, their identity online. And you&rsquo;ll have started it for them before they could even walk.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lo-faq-item">
        <div class="lo-faq-q">What if my child's exact name isn't available?</div>
        <p class="lo-faq-a">You can get creative &mdash; add a middle name, a family name, or a nickname. Many parents use formats like firstnamelastname.com, babyfirstname.com, or a family surname. There&rsquo;s almost always a great option available. Search for variations right here on the site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lo-faq-item">
        <div class="lo-faq-q">What does the book actually look like?</div>
        <p class="lo-faq-a">It&rsquo;s a beautiful, private website at their .com &mdash; like a personal magazine for your family. It has sections for birth story, month-by-month milestones, unlimited photos, letters to your child, family recipes, and a sealed Time Vault for messages to open when they&rsquo;re older. You can see a real example using the &ldquo;See a Live Demo Book&rdquo; link above.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lo-faq-item">
        <div class="lo-faq-q">Is the book private? Who can see it?</div>
        <p class="lo-faq-a">Yes &mdash; the site is password protected. Only people you share the password with can view it. You control who sees your family&rsquo;s story.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lo-faq-item">
        <div class="lo-faq-q">What happens after the first year?</div>
        <p class="lo-faq-a">After your introductory year at $29, the plan renews at $49.99/year (about $4.17/month). You can cancel anytime from your account &mdash; if you cancel, your book goes private but your domain stays registered until it expires. You can always re-activate later.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lo-faq-item">
        <div class="lo-faq-q">Can I give this as a baby shower gift?</div>
        <p class="lo-faq-a">Absolutely &mdash; it&rsquo;s one of the most popular ways people use Legacy Odyssey. You buy a gift for $29, and the recipient redeems it to pick their own domain and set up their book. Head to the <a href="/gift" style="color:#c8a96e;">Gift page</a> to get started.</p>
      </div>
